article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 49, Kentucky Wesleyan 0
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Jeremy Moses threw for five touchdowns and completed 25-of-34 passes to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 49-0 win over Kentucky Wesleyan on Saturday night. Dominiq Edison caught four passes for 92 yards and three touchdowns for the Lumberjacks (3-3). Aaron Rhea caught three passes for 41 yards and two touchdowns. Roderic Warren hauled in eight passes from Moses for 87 yards. Kentucky Wesleyan (2-4) only racked up 147 yards total offense in the nonconference loss. Chris Owen completed 10-of-18 passes for 45 yards, one interception and no touchdowns. Vincent Pervis ran the ball eight times for 79 yards in the game for the Lumberjacks. Je'Sea Godfrey rushed for 44 yards for the Panthers.
